The paper proposes a new architecture for efficient sequence modelling using a U-Net with causal convolutions. This is a topic that is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), signal processing (cs.SD), speech and natural language processing (cs.CL), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and social and information networks (cs.SI). However, given the focus on deep learning and neural networks, as well as the specific tasks of language and audio generation, cs.LG and cs.SD are the most likely sub-categories.
